The paper deals with joint modeling of language and vision, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of canonical correlation analysis (CCA) and regularization techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper specifically mentions multimodal data representation, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
